XML:
Extensible Markup Language 
XML Carries both data and metadata.

XML used in :
1. Data Exchange (using SOAP or REST)
2. Configuration file


XSD: XML Schema Defination:
XSD deines the grammer or a blue print for XML Document.

XML Follows XSD  --> Then that's a Valid XML Document

When to use XSD?
XSD file is a contract between two applications for Exchanging messages.
If no XSD provided then Application1 can send any data to Application2 or vise versa